This paper deals with the capacity of a communication channel, specifically the Gaussian cognitive interference channel. It presents outer bounds and inner bounds for this channel, which are techniques commonly used in information theory and communication engineering. The paper also evaluates achievable rate regions and provides numerical evaluations and comparisons. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), followed by cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.SI (Signal Processing), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
